summary: This is a tip submission form dated April 12, 2021, addressed to the FBI, concerning the investigation of Ghislaine Maxwell for human trafficking. The tipster claims to have information about Maxwell and also wishes to discuss a personal matter. The form includes structured questions and answers about the alleged violation.

persons.name: Ghislaine Maxwell
persons.context: Identified as a 'trafficker' in a human trafficking investigation tip submitted to the FBI. The tipster claims to have talked with several of her associates.

events.title: Tip submission to FBI
events.description: An individual submits a tip to the FBI via its website concerning the investigation of Ghislaine Maxwell for human trafficking.

keyFacts: A tip was submitted to the FBI on April 12, 2021, regarding Ghislaine Maxwell and a human trafficking investigation.
The tipster identifies Ghislaine Maxwell as a 'trafficker' and claims to have spoken with several of her associates.
The tipster indicates they do not know specific victims or locations, but the victim retains control of their own identification and travel documents.
The form includes a redacted complainant section, indicating the tipster's identity is withheld from the document extract.
